    <title>Tropical Fano Schemes</title>
    <summary>  We define a tropical version $F_d$(trop X) of the Fano Scheme $F_d(X)$ of a
projective variety $X\subset \mathbb P^n$. We focus on $d=1$ and compare it
with the tropicalization of $F_1(X)$. In general we have that trop
$F_1(X)\subset F_1$(trop $X)$. We construct linear spaces $L$ such that the
containment is strict and show that instead for a toric variety trop
$F_1(X)=F_1($trop $X)$. Finally we prove that $F_1($trop $X)$ is the support of
a polyhedral complex contained in trop $\mathbb G(1,n)$.
</summary>
